{"type":"message","id":"165c3cf6","parentId":"b770adb4","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:18:50.571Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Tuesday, April 21st, 2026 - 3:18 AM (UTC) / 2026-04-21 03:18 UTC"}],"timestamp":1776741530559}}
{"type":"message","id":"2baa1784","parentId":"165c3cf6","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:18:57.672Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me read the session startup files as instructed in AGENTS.md. I need to read SOUL.md, USER.md, and check for recent memory files.","thinkingSignature":"48ce1ccce1674e5e643620654c91d5a9f27ac367d2af54cb12e12c2440596c54"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bfuq3dcpdkjz_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bfuq3dcpdkjz_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bfuq3dcpdkjz_3","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator/memory/2026-04-21.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":210,"output":164,"cacheRead":9977,"cacheWrite":5906,"totalTokens":16257,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776741530572,"responseId":"06361f9c5776612bc5a0e0aaf2c26c63"}}
{"type":"message","id":"414272ec","parentId":"2baa1784","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:18:57.871Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bfuq3dcpdkjz_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\nWant a sharper version? See [SOUL.md Personality Guide](/concepts/soul).\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776741537849}}
{"type":"message","id":"e88ddb83","parentId":"414272ec","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:18:57.894Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bfuq3dcpdkjz_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:**\n- **What to call them:**\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:**\n- **Notes:**\n\n## Context\n\n- **Project:** MAIY Tech Hub (IT knowledge blog — Next.js 14 frontend + Fastify/MongoDB backend)\n- **GitLab:** maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub (frontend, maiy-hub/maiy-tech-hub-be (backend)\n- **VPS:** 103.253.21.139\n- **Admin:** admin@maiy.tech / maiy2026\n\n## Preferences\n\n- **Yêu cầu mới:** Luôn dùng prompt-optimizer để làm rõ trước → xác nhận với user → mới làm\n- Không gõ code trực tiếp — dùng spawn agent workflow\n- Không dùng PostgreSQL — chỉ MongoDB\n- Agent ecosystem: local only, không push lên GitLab\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776741537872}}
{"type":"message","id":"6a994186","parentId":"e88ddb83","timestamp":"2026-04-21T03:18:57.900Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bfuq3dcpdkjz_3","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory - 2026-04-21\n\n## DTLX Dashboard - Sidebar Fix (Session 2026-04-20)\n\n### Problem\n4 layout bugs reported by user:\n1. Sidebar bị \"trôi\" khi cuộn trang\n2. Content lấn sang trái (đè Sidebar)\n3. Header/Sidebar không đồng bộ\n4. Tooltip/Dropdown lệch tọa độ\n\n### Root Cause\nSidebar nằm trong `.main-area` có `overflow-y: auto` → cuộn theo content.\nTemplate có `.page-content { margin-left: var(--bs-sidenav-width) }` nhưng không đủ.\n\n### Final Fix (CSS only)\n**AdminLayout.jsx** structure:\n- `.sidenav-menu` → `position: fixed; left: 0; top: 0; height: 100vh; z-index: 100; overflow-y: auto`\n- `.main-area` → `padding-left: 240px; height: 100vh; overflow-y: auto; transition: padding-left 0.3s ease`\n\n**index.css** additions:\n- Condensed: `padding-left: 72px`\n- Expanded: `padding-left: 240px`\n- Logo area inside `.main-area` (not inside sidebar)\n\n### Git Workflow\n1. `git checkout develop && git pull`\n2. `git checkout feat/cms-driving-training-design`\n3. `git merge develop`\n4. `git push`\n5. User tạo MR thủ công: https://gitlab.com/ahv-dtlx/ahv-dtlx-frontend/-/merge_requests/new?source_branch=feat/cms-driving-training-design\n\n### Key Files Modified (DTLX Frontend)\n- `src/layouts/AdminLayout.jsx` - structure\n- `src/index.css` - sidebar + main-area CSS\n\n### VPS Services\n- DTLX Frontend: http://103.253.21.139:3002 (running)\n- DTLX Backend: http://103.253.21.139:5555 (running)\n- MAIY Frontend: http://103.253.21.139:3000 (running - DO NOT STOP)\n- MAIY Backend: http://103.253.21.139:4000 (running)\n\n### DTLX Login Issue\n- Backend database appears empty (no users)\n- Login credentials don't work\n- `admin123@gmail.com` / `123456` fails\n- MongoDB `dtlx-mongo` container at port 27017\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1776741537895}}
