{"type":"message","id":"cab7cce1","parentId":"969a4641","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:32:28.741Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config is invalid because of an unrecognized key \"routing\". The current version of OpenClaw on the VPS doesn't support the \"routing\" key. I need to remove that key and use the proper structure.\n\nLet me look at how the routing was configured in the original config - it was in the `routing.routes` section. I need to move that routing config into the agents' `match` field directly.\n\nActually, looking at the original config structure, the routing was under a separate `routing` key, but the current version of openclaw on the VPS doesn't support it. I need to restructure the config to put the routing information directly in each agent's config.\n \nNow I'm checking the current VPS openclaw version - it's 2026.4.15, but the original machine is running 2026.4.9, which does support the routing key. The issue is that the VPS version is newer but has different config schema requirements. Let me examine the original config structure more carefully to understand how routing was actually implemented. I'm realizing the version mismatch is the issue—the VPS has 2026.4.15 while the original machine has 2026.4.9, and the routing key might not be supported in the newer version. Rather than trying to downgrade, I should restructure the config to put the routing information directly in each agent's config under the channels section, then remove the top-level routing key entirely.","thinkingSignature":"375ff7edfd3fd34dff7082018a94189098c0e1c3de75a97ebbda39ea83e80288"},{"type":"text","text":"Config có key `\"routing\"` không recognized — cần fix. Dùng cấu trúc channels trực tiếp:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e31eo2u0zy5x_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/openclaw-vps2-fixed.json","content":"{\n  \"meta\": {\n    \"lastTouchedVersion\": \"2026.4.15\",\n    \"lastTouchedAt\": \"2026-04-21T04