{"type":"message","id":"2551feae","parentId":"1eaca1d7","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:45:41.862Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OpenClaw is installed. Now let me start the gateway. But I need to handle the env vars properly. Let me create a startup script that sets the env vars and starts the gateway.\n\nActually, looking at the current setup, the issue is that env vars are only set in bashrc, but the gateway needs them at runtime. Since openclaw reads env vars from the environment at startup, I need to make sure they're set.\n\nLet me create a systemd service or a simple startup script that sets the env vars and starts the gateway.Actually, a simpler approach would be to write the env vars to a file that gets sourced, and then start the gateway. Or I can use the openclaw env vars in the startup command.Let me create a startup script.","thinkingSignature":"9944dc47df79b54e2aa0b90b78b60822ee5703ec07d708f098f485b1ca18b661"},{"type":"text","text":"OpenClaw OK. Tạo script khởi động với env vars:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_q034fq06zokd_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'cat > /root/start-openclaw.sh << '\\''EOF'\\''\n#!/bin/bash\nexport AHVHOLDING_API_KEY=\"sk-3d8edc47e4037bc4-w85g8t-b82baf0b\"\nexport GITLAB_TOKEN=\"glpat-rjgwaQjEp7hL_skbf8lXamM6MQpvOjEKdTpsNWJ5Zw8.01.171o9yg1e\"\nexport TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=\"8605080868:AAFFvDZs3YwWfxaLgW7Lgj42ANwyFIzmFT8\"\nexport STITCH_API_KEY=\"AQ.Ab8RN6KimOxDQ4kNCgR68MBTO9qonEhjKMoCfu744Y4dWUblAg\"\nexport CONFLUENCE_URL=\"https://dtlx.atlassian.net/wiki\"\nexport CONFLUENCE_EMAIL=\"dqcuong.work@gmail.com\"\nexport CONFLUENCE_TOKEN=\"ATATT3xFfGF03z7i01Hgl_4UzecsdxxBKCs10EFmrVwCmT1zeLPRxhkOKMv5eIqgKbTWPdTISeYkx7YdcdBkDy9_sduO2Rlu95A6XHfnFL3efXUCqva3JyFNVFAoFIYGqSX_Jvw4oc7JOaVVEjfpZhRd3DebLI_93JjEOGcliM_alSWdh01RY9c=44ED3599\"\nexec openclaw gateway start\nEOF\nchmod +x /root/start-openclaw.sh &