{"type":"message","id":"3c081b6a","parentId":"8cc4e3a5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:47:31.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - the gateway process is running but it's not listening on any TCP port except SSH and DNS. The issue is that the gateway process is not properly starting its HTTP server. This could be because:\n\n1. The config has errors\n2. The gateway is crashing silently\n3. The port is already in use by another process\n\nLet me try a completely fresh approach. Let me kill all openclaw processes and start with a simpler config that only has the essential parts.\n\nActually, wait. I see the gateway processes are running (344139 and 344289) but they might be the old pnpm ones. Let me check if the npm-installed openclaw binary exists and if those processes are using the right binary.","thinkingSignature":"8679e9949f762eb786ad0d89093ff2e147448e57071fafde2ad5e729130d6af2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3rmgtll4b0km_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'cat /proc/$(pgrep openclaw-gateway | head -1)/maps 2>/dev/null | grep openclaw | head -3 && echo \"---\" && readlink /proc/$(pgrep openclaw-gateway | head -1)/exe 2>/dev/null'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":279,"output":274,"cacheRead":76627,"cacheWrite":506,"totalTokens":77686,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776746844480,"responseId":"0636345d61c714f912a73c8fd65b1f46"}}
