{"type":"message","id":"6ec7be8e","parentId":"85a84a88","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:51:32.735Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The gateway is not listening and all node processes are gone. This is very frustrating. The SSH connection keeps timing out.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Let me check if maybe the config is being read from a different location, or if the gateway has a different config file it prefers.\n\nActually, I think the issue might be simpler than I thought. Looking at the VPS, it had openclaw installed before (from the existing gateway at PID 2423). The old config might have been loaded from somewhere else, and the new one I uploaded isn't being picked up.\n\nLet me check what config file the current gateway process is using.Actually, you know what, let me just accept that there are some SSH connectivity issues and try a more targeted approach. \n\nI'm wondering if the gateway is actually running but binding to a different port than expected, or if it's listening on a Unix socket instead of TCP. Let me check what files the gateway process has open to see where it's actually listening.","thinkingSignature":"0787d9cb3b1c359f82195605691715adea50ab0038f8ddce443429b59e7926d1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8k2opqrrz6n2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'cat /proc/$(pgrep -f openclaw-gateway | head -1)/environ 2>/dev/null | tr \"\\0\" \"\\n\" | grep -E \"PORT|HOST|CONFIG\" | head -10'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":91,"output":318,"cacheRead":83078,"cacheWrite":595,"totalTokens":84082,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776747084777,"responseId":"0636354e018259e7c922652da71ed758"}}
