{"type":"message","id":"9dddda2a","parentId":"0e5109fd","timestamp":"2026-04-21T04:52:10.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Even locally on 127.0.0.1:18789, the gateway is not listening. So the gateway is definitely not starting the HTTP server.\n\nBut the Telegram bot is connected (getUpdates returns OK). This means the openclaw gateway is partially running - it's connecting to Telegram's API but not starting the local HTTP server.\n\nThis is very unusual. Let me check if maybe the gateway has a different startup mode or if the HTTP server is disabled.\n\nWait - let me re-read the config. Maybe the `gateway.mode` being \"local\" has some specific meaning in this version.\n\nActually, I just thought of something. Looking at the config-health.json from earlier:\n\n\nThe gateway was using a completely different config file - one with only 2783 bytes from April 8, not the current 28281-byte version. That older config must be what's actually running right now. The new config I uploaded isn't being picked up because the system is reading from that legacy file instead. The issue is that the health checker uses a hash to validate the config, and since the old config on the VPS had a completely different hash, my new version is being rejected. I need to either reset the health config so the gateway accepts the new 28281-byte version, or find another way to make it reload the actual current config.","thinkingSignature":"bb5e1efed79c29bb164e46d9022594f7834b49a96f79854b58d97c6bd6a172ac"},{"type":"text","text":"Gateway đang chạy nhưng dùng config cũ. Fix bằng cách clear health config:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_s2jjigsskzmz_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'echo \"{\\\"entries\\\":{}}\" > /root/.openclaw/logs/config-health.json && echo \"Health config cleared\"'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","mod