{"type":"message","id":"780ab078","parentId":"ca12fc5e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T05:20:08.875Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"No API root found. Let me check the gateway log to see what endpoints are available.\n\nActually, let me take a step back. The issue might be that the openclaw CLI on the VPS is having trouble connecting to the gateway. Let me check if maybe the openclaw CLI is using a different port or address by default.\n\nActually, I just realized something. When I run `openclaw --version`, it works quickly. But when I run `openclaw pairing approve` or `openclaw status`, it hangs. This suggests that the gateway-related commands hang because they're trying to connect to the gateway (which is running) but something is blocking the connection.\n\nWait - the gateway is running as a systemd service and binding to `127.0.0.1:18789`. \n\nThe CLI is running on the same machine, so it should be able to reach it. But maybe the CLI is using a different port or looking for the gateway in the wrong place. Let me check the openclaw config on the VPS to see what gateway settings are configured there.","thinkingSignature":"758774e59fb8e69e328c8d9a43ae0139939e46125636b7200fa61ab7e4e7d648"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pkyz9yc29pdm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sshpass -p '0zDxl1N36E(p@J' ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no root@161.248.81.138 'cat /root/.openclaw/openclaw.json | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); gw=d.get('\\''gateway'\\'',{}); print(json.dumps(gw, indent=2))\"'","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":83,"output":333,"cacheRead":98928,"cacheWrite":812,"totalTokens":100156,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776748800696,"responseId":"06363c02838a1f54156b6b726e3ffb75"}}
